    <h2>Who Should Use Writesonic?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Freelance writers & bloggers</strong> who need fast, SEO-optimized first drafts</li>
      <li><strong>Small business owners</strong> who can't afford Jasper's $49/mo price tag</li>
      <li><strong>SEO professionals & agencies</strong> needing keyword-optimized content at scale</li>
      <li><strong>E-commerce store owners</strong> who need bulk product descriptions</li>
      <li><strong>Content marketers on a budget</strong> looking for the best bang-for-buck AI writer</li>
      <li><strong>Social media managers</strong> creating daily content across platforms</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who Should Skip It?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Enterprise teams</strong> needing deep brand voice control — Jasper is better here</li>
      <li><strong>Users who only need occasional AI help</strong> — just use ChatGPT</li>
      <li><strong>Fiction writers</strong> — Writesonic is built for marketing content, not novels</li>
      <li><strong>Teams needing extensive collaboration</strong> — limited compared to Jasper or Notion AI</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Verdict</h2>
    <p>Writesonic has earned its place as one of the best value AI writing tools in 2026. The Article Writer 6.0 with real-time web data is genuinely impressive — it produces more accurate, better-researched content than most competitors. Chatsontic adds extra value as a standalone ChatGPT alternative. And at $16/month for the Individual plan, it's hard to argue with the price.</p>
    <p>Is it perfect? No. The content still needs human editing, the UI could be cleaner, and enterprise teams will find Jasper's brand features more robust. But for freelancers, small businesses, bloggers, and content marketers looking for an affordable, feature-rich AI writing platform, Writesonic is one of the best choices you can make in 2026.</p>
