    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Is Writesonic free to use?</h3>
    <p>Yes! Writesonic offers a free plan with 10,000 words per month and access to basic templates and Chatsontic. No credit card required. You can use it indefinitely for light content needs.</p>

    <h3>What is Chatsontic?</h3>
    <p>Chatsontic is Writesonic's conversational AI assistant — similar to ChatGPT but enhanced with real-time Google search, image generation, and voice command support. It can answer questions about current events, help with research, and generate content conversationally. It's included free with all Writesonic plans.</p>

    <h3>Writesonic vs. Jasper AI — which is better?</h3>
    <p>It depends on your needs and budget. Writesonic is significantly more affordable ($16/month vs. $49/month) and includes real-time web search that Jasper lacks. Jasper excels at brand voice consistency and team collaboration. For most individual users and small teams, Writesonic delivers better value. For larger teams with strict brand guidelines, Jasper may be the better choice.</p>

    <h3>Does Writesonic support SEO optimization?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely. Writesonic includes built-in keyword research, SEO meta tag generation, real-time content optimization suggestions, and native integration with Surfer SEO. The Article Writer 6.0 is specifically designed to produce SEO-friendly content with proper heading structure, keyword usage, and readability.</p>

    <h3>Can Writesonic write entire blog posts?</h3>
    <p>Yes. The Article Writer 6.0 can generate complete blog posts up to 5,000 words. You provide a topic and brief, and it creates an outline, researches current information, and writes the full article with citations. While the output usually needs editing, it provides a solid first draft that saves hours.</p>

    <h3>What languages does Writesonic support?</h3>
    <p>Writesonic supports content generation in over 25 languages, including English, Spanish, French, German, Portuguese, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Chinese, Hindi, Arabic, and more.</p>

